# CLAUDE.md — [Your Name]'s Development Environment

## Session Startup
1. Read project-level `CLAUDE.md` if it exists
2. Read `tasks/todo.md` and `tasks/lessons.md` — resume where you left off
3. Check CLAUDE.md freshness (run `/ccc:refresh` if stale)
4. Greet briefly, mention active tasks if any

## Environment
- **Shell:** zsh | **Editor:** Claude Code
- **CC Commander:** v2.1.0 (aggregator mode — 16 vendor packages)
- **Package manager:** npm/pnpm
- **Task system:** tasks/ directory (todo.md, lessons.md, specs)

## Coding Standards
- Strict mode. Functional style preferred.
- No unnecessary comments. Code is self-documenting.
- Error handling: fail fast, throw early, catch at boundaries.
- Tests: write them. Pick a framework and stick with it.

## Workflow

### Operating Model
You think. I execute. When uncertain: surface options with tradeoffs.

### Scope Discipline
Push back on ambitious plans. Ship small wins. 100 lines > 1000 lines when both work.

### Anti-Sycophancy
If something looks wrong, say so. Propose alternatives. Don't agree just because I suggested it.

### Corrective Framing
"You should be doing X — are you still?" over "Remember to do X"

### Evals Before Specs (ALL non-trivial work)
Define success criteria BEFORE the spec: evals > spec > plan > implement > verify.

### Spec-Based Development (ALL features >1 day)
1. **Spec first:** Ask 5-7 questions > write `tasks/spec-YYYYMMDD.md`
2. **New session:** Execute from spec in fresh context
3. **Plan mode** for any task with 3+ steps

### Subagent Strategy
- Use subagents liberally — keep main context clean
- One task per subagent. Parallel when independent.
- Never switch models mid-session — use subagents instead

### Tool Awareness (Critical)
- **Re-read after edit:** Always re-read a file after editing it. Tool results may be truncated to ~2,000 bytes — never assume a tool call succeeded without verifying.
- **Context decay:** Re-read files if >10 messages since last read. Your memory of file contents degrades as conversation grows. Treat file state as volatile, not cached.
- **File read budget:** Read tool caps at 2,000 lines. Use `offset`/`limit` for large files. Never assume you have read the entire file if it exceeds 2,000 lines.
- **One source of truth:** Never duplicate state across files. Pick one canonical location, reference it everywhere. Duplicated state drifts.

### Anti-Patterns to Avoid
- **Kitchen sink session:** Don't cram unrelated tasks into one session. Use `/clear` between topics or spawn subagents.
- **Over-specified CLAUDE.md:** Include architecture and principles, NOT line-by-line instructions. Trust the model with discretion.
- **Trust-then-verify gap:** Always verify after implementation. Never mark done without checking the actual output.
- **Infinite exploration:** Set a scope. 3 searches max before committing to an approach. Don't spiral.

### Context Optimization
- Use `/btw` for side questions that don't need to pollute the main context.
- Use `Ctrl+G` to open the current plan in your editor for review.
- Add to CLAUDE.md: "When compacting, always preserve: [list your critical context here]"
- Use `@path/to/import` in CLAUDE.md to compose from multiple source files at load time.

### Dialectic Review (Important Decisions)
For architecture choices or expensive-to-reverse decisions:
spawn FOR agent + AGAINST agent + Referee.

### Verification (MANDATORY before marking done)
- [ ] Feature works end-to-end
- [ ] No type/build errors
- [ ] No console errors
- [ ] Committed with conventional commit message
- [ ] Lessons captured in `tasks/lessons.md`

### Operationalize Every Fix
After fixing a bug: write class-level tests, sweep codebase for siblings, update CLAUDE.md.

### Self-Improvement
- After ANY correction: update `tasks/lessons.md` immediately
- Review lessons at session start
- Write rules that prevent the same mistake twice

## Core Principles
- **Simplicity First.** Minimal code, minimal impact.
- **No Laziness.** Root causes only. Senior developer standards.
- **Research Before Build.** Check npm, GitHub, existing libs first.
- **Evals Before Specs.** Define "done" and "broken" before writing code.
- **Check Skills First.** Search `SKILLS-INDEX.md` before building from scratch.
- **Boring Solutions Win.** 100 lines when 100 suffice over 1000 lines with abstractions.

## Aggregator Ecosystem
CC Commander aggregates 16 vendor packages via git submodules in `vendor/`.
Smart orchestrator picks the best tool: capability 50% + stars 15% + recency 15% + user pref 20%.
Auto-updates weekly via GitHub Actions.

